{
  "name": "Agent Memory — Session Save",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Final memory sweep: drafts gate, scoring, auto-promote, auto-crystallize, evolution nudges.",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check if this session produced meaningful state changes (task progress, new decisions, problem resolutions, or skill flags). If the session was only Q&A, comparison, research, or exploration without decisions — skip saving and report: 📝 No memory changes. If meaningful changes occurred: 1) Update agent-memory/memory.md — final refresh of Task_Ledger, Decisions_In_Force, Recent_Lessons, and Skill_Flags. 2) Evaluate all files in agent-memory/drafts/ through the Save/Discard Gate (novel + recur + non-trivial, 2/3 = save). For passing drafts: append to agent-memory/playbook.md (with Applied=0, Prevented=0) and delete the draft. For failing drafts: delete the draft. 3) Score increment: scan playbook.md for cases that were relevant this session. If a case's fix was actively used → increment its Applied column. If recognizing a case's trigger helped avoid the problem → increment its Prevented column. 4) Auto-promote: scan playbook.md for cases with Applied >= 3. For each qualifying case, create agent-memory/knowledge/{case-id}.md with full detail (trigger, fix, domain, evidence, score). Remove the case from playbook.md. Add the case ID to Recent_Lessons in memory.md. 5) Auto-crystallize: after promotion, count promoted knowledge files per domain in agent-memory/knowledge/. If any domain has 3+ files (including previously promoted ones), auto-create agent-memory/knowledge/{domain}-pattern.md that summarizes the common trigger/fix pattern across those cases. Safeguard: only merge cases that share both domain AND at least one trigger keyword. Report the crystallization but do NOT require user confirmation. 6) Archive check: if any playbook case has Applied+Prevented >= 5 AND was not used in the last 30 days → move it to agent-memory/knowledge/archive-playbook.md (create file if needed). 7) If any Skill_Flag has sufficient evidence, note a proposal in agent-memory/skill-log.md. 8) Evolution nudges: a) If skill-log.md has proposals with status=proposed → '🔧 Skill improvement pending: {skill} — say \"apply skill proposal\" to update the skill file.' b) If any Skill_Flag has 0 successes after 3+ sessions → '⚠️ Skill {skill} still underperforming — consider reviewing the skill file.' 9) Report: 📝 Session saved: [files updated, cases added/scored/promoted/crystallized/archived, proposals noted]."
  }
}
